notes: PA de Silva 145, highest ever score for Sri Lanka in ODIs (previous best ST Jayasuriya 140 v NZ at Bloemfontein 08/12/1994), first ever century for Sri Lanka in the World Cup.
Gurusinha dropped by Onyango off Karim when on 79.
Gurusinha hits a ball outside the ground and the ball is lost. Umpires provide a replacement ball.
de Silva, and then Ranatunga crossed 5000 runs in ODI cricket, - the first two from Sri Lanka to do so - during this innings.
Sri Lanka 398 runs, highest ever score in ODI history. Sri Lanka now have the top score, but also have 6 of the top 12 totals scored against them.
SO Tikolo 96, highest ever score for Kenya.

milestones.description: de Silva and Gurusinha's 183-run partnership is SL's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 172 between de Silva and Gurusinha
Chudasama and Otieno's 47-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 1st wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 41 between Chudasama and Otieno
Steve Tikolo and Hitesh Modi's 137-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 34 between Otieno and Hitesh Modi
Martin Suji and David Tikolo's 8-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 8th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 1 between Martin Suji and David Tikolo
de Silva has become the top scorer for SL in ODIs with 5086 runs, going past Ranatunga's 4967
Steve Tikolo has become the top scorer for KENYA in ODIs with 196 runs, going past Otieno's 133
Steve Tikolo has scored 2 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for KENYA breaking Odumbe's record
Steve Tikolo has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (4) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Steve Tikolo's 1
de Silva's 145 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for SL), surpassing Jayasuriya's 140
Steve Tikolo's 96 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for KENYA), surpassing Otieno's 85
de Silva has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (86) in an innings in ODIs for SL, going past Jayasuriya's 72
Steve Tikolo has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (56) in an innings in ODIs for KENYA, going past Otieno's 38
Sri Lanka's 398 is the highest total in ODIs, surpassing England's 363
de Silva and Gurusinha's 183-run partnership is SL's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 172 between Gurusinha and de Silva
Steve Tikolo and Hitesh Modi's 137-run partnership is KENYA's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 102 between Odumbe and Otieno
Martin Suji has conceded the most runs in an innings (85) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Thomas Odoyo's record of 58
Rajab Ali has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (6) for KENYA, going past Chudasama
